(1037, 'VIASPACE Expands Board With Two Independent Directors', '', '\r\n<P>PASADENA, CA?October 25, 2005?VIASPACE Inc. (OTCBB: VSPC), a company that works to transform proven space and defense technologies from NASA and the Department of Defense into hardware and software solutions that solve today''s complex problems, announced today the addition of two members to its Board of Directors, Dr. Joel Balbien and Mr. Aaron Levy.&nbsp; Dr. Balbien was elected as Chairperson of the Audit Committee and of the Governance and Nominating Committee and will also serve as a member of the Compensation Committee.&nbsp; Mr. Levy was elected as Chairperson of the Compensation Committee and will also serve as a member of the Audit Committee and of the Governance and Nominating Committee. </P>\r\n<P>Dr. Balbien is Managing Member of Los Angeles-based Smart Technology Ventures III, a $175 million SBIC venture capital fund focusing on telecommunications, broadband infrastructure, software, and semiconductors.&nbsp; He also serves on the Board of Directors of Sonics, Inc., STM Power, and on the executive Committee of the Board of Kreido Laboratories.&nbsp; Previously, Dr. Balbien was Senior Financial Officer at Smart Technology Ventures, and served as Assistant Treasurer and Chief Economist at Southern California Gas Company.&nbsp; Dr. Balbien received a Ph.D. in Economics from Caltech and is a Chartered Financial Analyst.</P>\r\n<P>Mr. Levy is the founder and CEO of Etech Ventures, a privately held organizational consulting firm founded in 1998.&nbsp; Etech is a turnaround specialist focused on private, pre-IPO and publicly traded high technology companies.&nbsp; Mr. Levy has extensive business background across multiple high tech industries and has served as Chairman, CEO, President and/or Director for several publicly traded Nasdaq high technology companies.&nbsp; He served as President of Luminent, Inc., a fiber optics components company, and Chairman, CEO and President of Dense-Pac Microsystems, specializing in high-density semiconductor memory for commercial and defense electronics. </P>\r\n<P>Mr. Levy is a US patent holder and the author of Digital Printing, published 3rd edition by Interquest in 2004.&nbsp; He received a Master of Science in Aerospace Engineering from Northrop University and a Bachelor of Science in Electrical Engineering from the University of California, Irvine.&nbsp; Mr. Levy served in the military and he is an FAA certified multi-engine commercial pilot and a flight instructor pilot.&nbsp;&nbsp; Mr. Levy is an elected honor member of Tau Beta Pi, Sigma Gamma Tau and Eta Kappa Nu, the national engineering, electrical and aerospace honor societies.&nbsp; Currently Mr. Levy is pursuing his Ph.D. in Leadership and Organizational Behavior at Walden University. </P>\r\n<P>Dr. Carl Kukkonen, Chief Executive Officer of VIASPACE, said,&nbsp; ?We are very pleased that Dr. Balbien and Mr. Levy have agreed to join our Board as independent directors. Dr. Balbien?s extensive background in finance and economics will be a major asset to the Board and to VIASPACE management as we continue to grow and develop our Company.&nbsp; Mr. Levy, with his wealth of management and engineering expertise, combined with his public company experience, will be an invaluable counsel.?</P>\r\n<P>About VIASPACE: Unparalleled Knowledge.&nbsp; Unparalleled Solutions.<BR>VIASPACE is a diversified technology company with knowledge and expertise in energy/fuel cells, microelectronics, sensors, homeland security & public safety, information & computational technology, and RFID. Founded in 1998 with the objective of transforming proven space and defense technologies from NASA and the Department of Defense into hardware and software solutions that solve today''s complex problems, VIASPACE benefits from important patent and software licenses from Caltech, which manages NASA?s Jet Propulsion Laboratory, and from relationships with research laboratories, universit