(1154, 'Cohen Independent Research Group Updates Coverage of VIASPACE', '', '<h5 align="center">COHEN INDEPENDENT RESEARCH GROUP UPDATES COVERAGE OF VIASPACE </h5><p>PASADENA, Calif., October 16, 2007 - VIASPACE Inc. (OTC Bulletin Board: VSPC - News), a company commercializing proven technologies from NASA and the US Department of Defense commented today on the updated research report from Cohen Independent Research Group, available on the Cohen website at www.cohenresearch.com.</p><p>VIASPACE CEO Dr. Carl Kukkonen states, &quot;Paul Cohen&#39;s team continues to perform a tremendous amount of research on VIASPACE as presented in their recent update, including a detailed financial analysis of our execution on our future performance goals.&quot;</p><p><br />The Cohen Independent Research Group is Wall Street&#39;s leading independent research firm, concentrating on emerging companies with strong management teams focused on shareholder value and sustainable competitive advantage.&nbsp;&nbsp; Cohen&#39;s research reports highlight the company&#39;s market opportunity, technology, management, competition and other key differentiators that may affect their long and short term valuation.&nbsp; Cohen focuses on those public companies that do not currently have Wall Street research analyst coverage.&nbsp; Cohen research reports are commissioned and paid for by the companies covered, or by third parties.</p><p><br />Kukkonen continues, &quot;VIASPACE commissioned and paid for the initial Cohen report to provide a resource for the public and our investors.&nbsp; VIASPACE continues to provide Company information to the Cohen team, but the research, analysis and their &quot;buy&quot; recommendation with a target price of $2.85 per share was done independently by Cohen.&quot;&nbsp; </p><p><br />About VIASPACE:&nbsp; Founded in 1998 to transform proven space and defense technologies from NASA and the Department of Defense into&nbsp; commercial&nbsp; hardware and software solution