(1155, 'VIASPACE Energy DMFCC Exhibits at Fuel Cell Seminar 2007 in San Antonio', '', '<h5 align="center">VIASPACE ENERGY/DIRECT METHANOL FUEL CELL CORPORATION<br />EXHIBIT AT FUEL CELL SEMINAR 2007 IN SAN ANTONIO</h5><p><br />PASADENA, CA -October 17, 2007-- VIASPACE Inc. (OTCBB: VSPC), a company dedicated to commercializing proven technologies from NASA and the US Department of Defense, announced today that its VIASPACE Energy Division, including subsidiary Direct Methanol Fuel Cell Corporation (DMFCC) are exhibitors at FC Seminar 2007,&nbsp; being held October 15-17, 2007 at the convention center in San Antonio, TX.&nbsp; </p><p><br />Dr. Carl Kukkonen, CEO of both VIASPACE and DMFCC, said, &quot;We are demonstrating our new VIASENSOR HS-1000 Relative Humidity sensor, as well as one of our fuel cartridges working with a direct methanol fuel cell made by Parker Hannifin. Other recent cartridge and valve connector prototypes will be on display.&nbsp; The booth will be manned by the VIASPACE Energy and DMFCC staff from the US. We have also set up private meetings with potential customers and partners on new development efforts, including Tyco Electronics.&quot;</p><p>VIASPACE Energy is focused on instrumentation for fuel cells and battery products. DMFCC focuses on producing and distributing methanol fuel cartridges designed to provide the energy source for laptop computers, cell phones and other portable electronic devices to be powered by direct methanol fuel cells.</p><p>Fuel cells are expected to gain a substantial market share because they offer longer operating time as compared to current lithium ion batteries and may be instantaneously recharged by simply replacing the disposable fuel cartridge.&nbsp; Leading OEMs have announced that they are developing direct methanol fuel cells for portable electronic applications.<br />&nbsp;<br />About VIASPACE:&nbsp; Originally founded in 1998 with the objective of transforming proven space and defense technologies from NASA and the Department of Defense into hardware and software solutions that solve today&#39;s complex problems, VIASPACE benefits from important patent and software licenses from Caltech, which manages NASA&#39;s Jet Propulsion Laboratory.&nbsp; </p><p>For more information, please visit www.VIASPACE.com, or contact Investor Relations, Dr. Jan Vandersande, Director of Communications at 800-517-8050, or IR@VIASPACE.com.&nbsp; For past press releases, please visit: http://www.viaspace.com/press_release.php.</p><p>Press contact: Carl Kukkonen 626-768-3360 <br />-----------------------------<br /><em>This news release includes forward-looking statements.&nbsp; These forward-looking statements relate to future events or our future performance and involve known and unknown risks, uncertainties and other factors that may cause our actual results, levels of activity, performance or achievements to be materially different from any future results, levels of activity, performance or achievements expressed or implied by these forward-looking statements.&nbsp; Such factors include the risks outlined in our periodic filings with the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission, including our Annual Report on Form 10-KSB, as amended, for the fiscal year ended December 31, 2006, and our Quarterly Report on Form 10-Q for the period ended June 30, 2007, as well as general economic and business conditions, the ability to acquire and develop specific projects and technologies, the ability to fund operations, changes in consumer and business consumption habits, and other factors over which VIASPACE has little or no control.</em></p>', '2007-10-17 00:00:00', '', '', 1, 1, 1155, 1),
(1156, 'Ballard Power Systems Orders VIASENSOR HS-1000 Humidity Sensor from VIASPACE Energy', '', '<h5 align="center">BALLARD POWER SYSTEMS ORDERS VIASENSOR HS-1000 HUMIDITY SENSOR FROM VIASPACE ENERGY </h5><p>PASADENA, CA.-October 22, 2007-VIASPACE Inc. (OTCBB: VSPC), a company that transforms proven space and defense technologies from NASA and the Department of Defense into hardware and software solutions, announced today that it has received an order for its VIASENSOR HS-1000 Relative Humidity sensor from Ballard Power Systems.&nbsp; </p><p>The performance of hydrogen fuel cells using a Polymer Electrolyte Membrane (PEM) depends on the moisture level of the membrane.&nbsp; The membrane only conducts protons when it is hydrated or moist.&nbsp; The moisture is provided by water vapor in the incoming air or hydrogen stream.&nbsp; The VIASENSOR HS-1000 humidity instrument will provide real-time measurements of the amount of water vapor in these gas streams.&nbsp; </p><p>VIASPACE CEO Carl Kukkonen stated, &quot;We are delighted to add Ballard Power Systems to our growing list of VIASENSOR HS-1000 customers. Ballard has significant facilities for development of hydrogen based fuel cells, and our demonstration of the HS-1000 several weeks ago at their facility has resulted in this order to more fully evaluate the HS-1000&#39;s capabilities. The HS-1000 is a leading edge, laser-based sensor with considerable improvement in accuracy and response time over other available instruments. Their feedback will be of great assistance in our future development of other models of the HS-1000 series instruments. We feel that this device will help Ballard more rapidly optimize fuel cell designs for various government and commercial research programs in which they may be engaged.&quot; </p><p>About VIASPACE:&nbsp; Founded in 1998 with the objective of transforming proven space and defense technologies from NASA and the Department of Defense into hardware and software solutions that solve today&#39;s complex problems, VIASPACE benefits from important patent and software licenses from Caltech, which manages NASA&#39;s Jet Propulsion Laboratory.&nbsp; </p><p>For more information, please visit www.VIASPACE.com, or contact Investor Relations, Dr. Jan Vandersande, Director of Communications at 800-517-8050, or IR@VIASPACE.com.&nbsp; For past press releases, please visit: http://www.viaspace.com/press_release.php.</p><p>Press contact: Carl Kukkonen 626-768-3360 <br />-----------------------------<br /><em>This news release includes forward-looking statements.&nbsp; These forward-looking statements relate to future events or our future performance and involve known and unknown risks, uncertainties and other factors that may cause our actual results, levels of activity, performance or achievements to be materially different from any future results, levels of activity, performance or achievements expressed or implied by these forward-looking statements.&nbsp; Such factors include the risks outlined in our periodic filings with the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission, including our Annual Report on Form 10-KSB, as amended, for the fiscal year ended December 31, 2006, and our Quarterly Report on Form 10-Q for the period ended June 30, 2007, as well as general economic and business conditions, the ability to acquire and develop specific projects and technologies, the ability to fund operations, changes in consumer and business consumption habits, and other factors over which VIASPACE has little or no control.</em></p>', '2007-10-22 00:00:00', '', '', 1, 1, 1156, 1),
(1157, 'VIASPACE Security Becomes a Reseller for DMT AIMS Radar Surveillance Solution', '', '<h5 align="center">VIASPACE SECURITY TO SELL AND SERVICE DMT RADAR SURVEILLANCE SYSTEM </h5><p>PASADENA, CA.-October 24, 2007-VIASPACE Inc. (OTCBB: VSPC), a company that transforms proven space and defense technologies from NASA and the Department of Defense into hardware and software solutions, announced today that its VIASPACE Security subsidy has signed&nbsp; an addendum to its teaming agreement with DMT (Detection Monitoring Technologies Ltd.) of Sterling Virginia..&nbsp; </p><p>DMT is a global leader in providing complete radar security solutions. The AIMS &quot;Area Intrusion Monitoring System&quot; family of radar security surveillance solutions was developed for wide area security, waterside security, base security, and border applications.&nbsp; The AIMS solution is based on an X-Band pulsed Doppler radar using advanced detection algorithms designed specifically to detect targets representing intrusion threats under wide area perimeter surveillance.&nbsp;&nbsp; The AIMS system is currently installed world-wide as an integral part of national and border patrol defenses.</p><p>The new addendum establishes specific terms between the companies for VIASPACE Security to re-sell AIMS hardware, to develop and sell software upgrades and to establish a services group for installation, set-up and maintenance of hardware and software comprising the AIMS system. VIASPACE Security may also integrate the AIMS system with other sensor technology extending both is functionality and capabilities as a fully integrated perimeter security monitoring solution. </p><p>VIASPACE CEO Carl Kukkonen stated &quot;We are impressed with the speed of implementation of this teaming agreement with DMT. They provide a proven hardware and software security solution that appears to be in great demand on a global basis. It is an ideal sensor fusion platform to leverage our SHINE (Spacecraft Health Inference Engine) inference engine and real time sensor fusion software technology allowing for many promising future business opportunities. We are currently recruiting additional staff to begin support for DMT and to get started on software upgrades for the AIMS system.&quot; </p><p>About VIASPACE:&nbsp; Founded in 1998 with the objective of transforming proven space and defense technologies from NASA and the Department of Defense into hardware and software solutions that solve today&#39;s complex problems, VIASPACE benefits from important patent and software licenses from Caltech, which manages NASA&#39;s Jet Propulsion Laboratory.&nbsp; For more information, please see www.VIASPACE.com, or contact Dr. Jan Vandersande, Director of Communications at 800-517-8050, or IR@VIASPACE.com.</p><p>About DMT:&nbsp; Detection Monitoring Technologies Ltd. is a leader in providing complete radar monitoring systems to the US government, defense contractors, commercial companies and friendly governments around the world.&nbsp; More information is on their website www.dmtllc.com.</p><p>Press contact: Carl Kukkonen 626-768-3360 <br />-----------------------------<br /><em>This news release includes forward-looking statements.&nbsp; These forward-looking statements relate to future events or our future performance and involve known and unknown risks, uncertainties and other factors that may cause our actual results, levels of activity, performance or achievements to be materially different from any future results, levels of activity, performance or achievements expressed or implied by these forward-looking statements.&nbsp; Such factors include the risks outlined in our periodic filings with the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission, including our Annual Report on Form 10-KSB, as amended, for the fiscal year ended December 31, 2006, and our Quarterly Report on Form 10-Q for the period ended June 30, 2007, as well as general economic and business conditions, the ability to acquire and develop specific projects and technologies, the ability to fund operations, changes in consumer and business consumption habits, and other factors over which VIASPACE has little or no control.</em></p>', '2007-10-24 00:00:00', '', '', 1, 1, 1157, 1),
(1158, 'Direct Methanol Fuel Cell Corporation Expands Global Strategy by Teaming with INER of Taiwan', '', '<h5 align="center">DIRECT METHANOL FUEL CELL CORPORATION EXPANDS GLOBAL STRATEGY BY TEAMING WITH INER OF TAIWAN </h5><p>PASADENA, CA -November 8, 2007-VIASPACE Inc. (OTCBB: VSPC) announced that the Institute of Nuclear Energy Research ( INER) of Taiwan and VIASPACE subsidiary Direct Methanol Fuel Cell Corporation (DMFCC) have signed a teaming agreement which includes collaboration on development of Direct Methanol Fuel Cell Corporation&#39;s line of fuel cell cartridges and other fuel cell products. INER is a key Taiwanese government sponsored research institute focused on the development of energy technology and products including fuel cells.</p><p>Dr. Carl Kukkonen, CEO of VIASPACE and DMFCC, stated &quot;Our teaming agreement with INER is a perfect example of DMFCC&#39;s continued expansion of its global business strategy.&nbsp; We are partnering with top organizations around the globe that have a good reputation and the trust of customers in their own markets.&nbsp; INER performs important research and development of fuel cells and fuel cell products in collaboration with major corporations in Taiwan.&quot;&nbsp; </p><p>VIASPACE is a growing company with proprietary technology, much of which was originally developed at the NASA Jet Propulsion Laboratory (JPL) and licensed from Caltech, which manages JPL for NASA.&nbsp; </p><p>Kukkonen continued, &quot;We are honored to have a relationship with INER.&nbsp; We believe that this teaming agreement will benefit both organizations and will help fuel cells reach the marketplace more quickly.&quot;&nbsp; </p><p>About VIASPACE:&nbsp; Originally founded in 1998 with the objective of transforming proven space and defense technologies from NASA and the Department of Defense into hardware and software solutions that solve today&#39;s complex problems, VIASPACE benefits from important patent and software licenses from Caltech, which manages NASA&#39;s Jet Propulsion Laboratory.&nbsp; For more information, please visit our website at www.VIASPACE.com, or contact for Investor Relations, Dr. Jan Vandersande, Director of Communications at 800-517-8050, or IR@VIASPACE.com.</p><p>Press contact: Carl Kukkonen 626-768-3360 <br />-----------------------------<br /><em>This news release includes forward-looking statements.&nbsp; These forward-looking statements relate to future events or our future performance and involve known and unknown risks, uncertainties and other factors that may cause our actual results, levels of activity, performance or achievements to be materially different from any future results, levels of activity, performance or achievements expressed or implied by these forward-looking statements.&nbsp; Such factors include the risks outlined in our periodic filings with the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission, including our Annual Report on Form 10-KSB, as amended, for the fiscal year ended December 31, 2006, and our Quarterly Report on Form 10-Q for the period ended June 30, 2007, as well as general economic and business conditions, the ability to acquire and develop specific projects and technologies, the ability to fund operations, changes in consumer and business consumption habits, and other factors over which VIASPACE has little or no control.</em></p>', '2007-11-08 00:00:00', '', '', 1, 1, 1158, 1),
(1159, 'VIASPACE Recieved Contract for IED Software Development', '', '<h5 align="center">VIASPACE RECEIVES CONTRACT FOR SOFTWARE DEVELOPMENT FOR A SUICIDE BOMB DETECTION SYSTEM</h5><p>PASADENA, CA-November 6, 2007-VIASPACE Inc. (OTCBB: VSPC), a company commercializing proven technologies from NASA and the US Department of Defense, reported that it has received a new contract from a defense contractor for software development for a suicide bomb detection system. </p><p>This is a new, multi-phased program for VIASPACE Security, a wholly-owned VIASPACE subsidiary. VIASPACE will provide the overall software architecture and development of specific algorithms and operational software needed for actual bomb detection. VIASPACE has an exclusive license from Caltech to commercialize NASA&#39;s SHINE real-time inference engine technology for most major applications including defense applications, homeland defense, maritime security and diagnostics/prognostics. </p><p>AJ Abdallat, President of VIASPACE Security, commented: &quot;We are pleased to begin this new effort in pursuit of a solution to the threat from suicide bombs. This is a serious problem, and we see this as a tremendous opportunity for VIASPACE Security. We believe that our sensor data fusion and SHINE inference engine technologies will play a key role in solutions to improve the detection of explosives carried by suicide bombers. &quot;</p><p>The suicide bomb detection program is one of several major initiatives on the part of the Department of Defense and the Department of Homeland Defense. VIASPACE Security is targeting this growing $20+ Billion market, pursuing opportunities where real-time sensor fusion technology and its high speed inference engine can deliver substantial benefit. </p><p>About VIASPACE:&nbsp; Originally founded in 1998 with the objective of transforming proven space and defense technologies from NASA and the Department of Defense into hardware and software solutions that solve today&#39;s complex problems, VIASPACE benefits from important patent and software licenses from Caltech, which manages NASA&#39;s Jet Propulsion Laboratory.&nbsp; </p><p>For more information, please visit www.VIASPACE.com, or contact Investor Relations, Dr. Jan Vandersande, Director of Communications at 800-517-8050, or IR@VIASPACE.com.&nbsp; For past press releases, please visit: http://www.viaspace.com/press_release.php.</p><p>Press contact: Carl Kukkonen 626-768-3360 <br />-----------------------------<br /><em>This news release includes forward-looking statements.&nbsp; These forward-looking statements relate to future events or our future performance and involve known and unknown risks, uncertainties and other factors that may cause our actual results, levels of activity, performance or achievements to be materially different from any future results, levels of activity, performance or achievements expressed or implied by these forward-looking statements.&nbsp; Such factors include the risks outlined in our periodic filings with the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission, including our Annual Report on Form 10-KSB, as amended, for the fiscal year ended December 31, 2006, and our Quarterly Report on Form 10-Q for the period ended June 30, 2007, as well as general economic and business conditions, the ability to acquire and develop specific projects and technologies, the ability to fund operations, changes in consumer and business consumption habits, and other factors over which VIASPACE has little or no control.</em></p>', '2007-11-06 00:00:00', '', '', 0, 1, 1159, 1),
(1160, 'VIASPACE Modernizes Website to Speed the Update of Customer, Partner and Shareholder Information and News', '', '<h5 align="center">VIASPACE Modernizes Website to speed the update of Customer, Partner and Shareholder information and news</h5><p>PASADENA, Calif., November 14, 2007 - VIASPACE Inc. (OTC Bulletin Board: VSPC - News), a company commercializing proven technologies from NASA and the US Department of Defense into hardware and software solutions, has recently invested in a major modernization of its website. VIASPACE is executing on both of its major strategies in clean energy and security, by increasing domestic and overseas marketing, expanding its global network of manufacturers and distributors, investigating opportunities for new battery and fuel cell testing products and security and sensor fusion applications, and working on additional new products based on potential customers&#39; inquiries.</p><p>Dr. Carl Kukkonen, CEO of VIASPACE and VIASPACE Security, stated, &quot;The rapid expansion of VIASPACE Energy as a business division has accelerated the growth of its fuel cell humidity sensor product line and direct methanol fuel cell cartridge business and allowed it to pursue new opportunities identified within the growing alternative energy market. VIASPACE Security has equally expanded its marketing efforts on a global basis in both inference engine and sensor fusion technology, has now teamed with a major radar/IR hardware platform manufacturer in the perimeter security sector and has been augmented several times in funding on its Advanced Cargo Screening Device contract from L3 Communications.&quot;</p><p>Dr. Kukkonen continued, &quot;VIASPACE has also recently signed new partnering agreements in Japan and Malaysia, added distributors in Japan, Korea, China, Malaysia, Israel and the Middle East and has licensed new technology from Caltech for both&nbsp; markets. Coupled with new, in-depth reports on the company and positive projections of its value, we felt it necessary to modernize our website to provide a more organized information flow to our many customers, partners and share holders on a more frequent basis. We are rapidly executing on our strategy in both business divisions, and we felt this website modernization would help us keep up with the larger flow of information and news.&quot; </p><p>About VIASPACE:&nbsp; Originally founded in 1998 with the objective of transforming proven space and defense technologies from NASA and the Department of Defense into hardware and software solutions that solve today&#39;s complex problems, VIASPACE benefits from important patent and software licenses from Caltech, which manages NASA&#39;s Jet Propulsion Laboratory. For more information, please visit our website at www.VIASPACE.com</p><p>Investor Relations contact: <br />Dr. Jan Vandersande, Director of Communications <br />800-517-8050<br />IR@VIASPACE.com</p><p>Press contact: <br />Dr. Carl Kukkonen, CEO<br />626-768-3360 <br />-----------------------------<br /><em>This news release includes forward-looking statements.&nbsp; These forward-looking statements relate to future events or our future performance and involve known and unknown risks, uncertainties and other factors that may cause our actual results, levels of activity, performance or achievements to be materially different from any future results, levels of activity, performance or achievements expressed or implied by these forward-looking statements.&nbsp; Such factors include the risks outlined in our periodic filings with the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission, including our Annual Report on Form 10-KSB, as amended, for the fiscal year ended December 31, 2006, and our Quarterly Report on Form 10-Q for the period ended June 30, 2007, as well as general economic and business conditions, the ability to acquire and develop specific projects and technologies, the ability to fund operations, changes in consumer and business consumption habits, and other factors over which VIASPACE has little or no control.</em></p>', '2007-11-14 00:00:00', '', '', 1, 1, 1160, 1);
