><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.5in; text-align: justify; text-indent: -0.25in; tab-stops: list .5in"><span style="color: black; font-family: Arial"><span><font size="3">&bull;</font><span style="font: 7pt/normal ''Times New Roman''; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span style="color: black"><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">11% internal electricity use</font></span></p><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">  </font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.5in; text-align: justify; text-indent: -0.25in; tab-stops: list .5in"><span style="color: black; font-family: Arial"><span><font size="3">&bull;</font><span style="font: 7pt/normal ''Times New Roman''; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span style="color: black"><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">84 million kwh of salable electricity</font></span></p><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">  </font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.5in; text-align: justify; text-indent: -0.25in; tab-stops: list .5in"><span style="color: black; font-family: Arial"><span><font size="3">&bull;</font><span style="font: 7pt/normal ''Times New Roman''; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span style="color: black"><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">Expected project lifetime 25+ years</font></span></p><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">  </font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.5in; text-align: justify; text-indent: -0.25in; tab-stops: list .5in"><span style="color: black; font-family: Arial"><span><font size="3">&bull;</font><span style="font: 7pt/normal ''Times New Roman''; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span style="color: black"><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">Fuel consumption--9 dry equivalent metric tons of Giant King Grass per hour</font></span></p><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">  </font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.5in; text-align: justify; text-indent: -0.25in; tab-stops: list .5in"><span style="color: black; font-family: Arial"><span><font size="3">&bull;</font><span style="font: 7pt/normal ''Times New Roman''; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span style="color: black"><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">Power plant co-located with 2,100 acre (832 hectare) Giant King Grass plantation</font></span></p><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">  </font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-align: justify"><span style="color: black"><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">&nbsp;</font></span></p><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">  </font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-align: justify"><font face="Times New Roman"><span style="color: black"><font size="3">Nicaragua</font></span><span style="color: black"><font size="3"> power plant and plantation status:</font></span></font></p><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">  </font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.5in; text-align: justify; text-indent: -0.25in; tab-stops: list .5in"><span style="color: black; font-family: Wingdings"><span><font size="3">&uuml;</font><span style="font: 7pt/normal ''Times New Roman''; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span style="color: black"><font face="Times New Roman"><font size="3">Prefeasibility study</font><span><font size="3">&nbsp; </font></span><font size="3">and business plan completed</font></font></span></p><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">  </font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.5in; text-align: justify; text-indent: -0.25in; tab-stops: list .5in"><span style="color: black; font-family: Wingdings"><span><font size="3">&uuml;</font><span style="font: 7pt/normal ''Times New Roman''; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span style="color: black"><font face="Times New Roman"><font size="3">Giant King Grass growing well in </font><font size="3">Nicaragua</font></font></span></p><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">  </font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.5in; text-align: justify; text-indent: -0.25in; tab-stops: list .5in"><span style="color: black; font-family: Wingdings"><span><font size="3">&uuml;</font><span style="font: 7pt/normal ''Times New Roman''; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span style="color: black"><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">Formal feasibility study completed</font></span></p><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">  </font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.5in; text-align: justify; text-indent: -0.25in; tab-stops: list .5in"><span style="color: black; font-family: Wingdings"><span><font size="3">&uuml;</font><span style="font: 7pt/normal ''Times New Roman''; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span style="color: black"><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">EPC contractor selected and contract signed</font></span></p><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">  </font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.5in; text-align: justify; text-indent: -0.25in; tab-stops: list .5in"><span style="color: black; font-family: Wingdings"><span><font size="3">&uuml;</font><span style="font: 7pt/normal ''Times New Roman''; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span style="color: black"><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">Power plant operator selected</font></span></p><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">  </font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.5in; text-align: justify; text-indent: -0.25in; tab-stops: list .5in"><span style="color: black; font-family: Wingdings"><span><font size="3">&uuml;</font><span style="font: 7pt/normal ''Times New Roman''; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span style="color: black"><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">Provisional Generation License applied for</font></span></p><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">  </font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.5in; text-align: justify; text-indent: -0.25in; tab-stops: list .5in"><span style="color: black; font-family: Wingdings"><span><font size="3">&uuml;</font><span style="font: 7pt/normal ''Times New Roman''; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span style="color: black"><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">Non-objection letter obtained from community</font></span></p><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">  </font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.5in; text-align: justify; text-indent: -0.25in; tab-stops: list .5in"><span style="color: black; font-family: Wingdings"><span><font size="3">&uuml;</font><span style="font: 7pt/normal ''Times New Roman''; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span style="color: black"><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">Non-objection letter obtained from environmental department</font></span></p><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">  </font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.5in; text-align: justify; text-indent: -0.25in; tab-stops: list .5in"><span style="color: black; font-family: Wingdings"><span><font size="3">&uuml;</font><span style="font: 7pt/normal ''Times New Roman''; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span style="color: black"><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">In progress with debt financers--banks</font></span></p><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">  </font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.5in; text-align: justify; text-indent: -0.25in; tab-stops: list .5in"><span style="color: black; font-family: Wingdings"><span><font size="3">&uuml;</font><span style="font: 7pt/normal ''Times New Roman''; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span style="color: black"><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">Local partners will provide half of the equity</font></span></p><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">  </font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.25in; text-align: justify"><span style="color: black"><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">&nbsp;</font></span></p><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">  </font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-align: justify"><span style="color: black"><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">Remaining items planned to be completed in coming months. Power plant construction and commissioning will take less than two years.</font></span></p><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">  </font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-align: justify"><span style="color: black"><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">&nbsp;</font></span></p><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">  </font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-align: justify"><span style="color: black"><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">At the conference, Dr. Kukkonen also held technical meetings, and met with potential new customers, suppliers and investors.</font></span></p><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">  </font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-align: justify"><span style="color: black"><font face="Times New Roman"><font size="3">VIASPACE Chairman, Dr. Kevin Schewe, commented, &ldquo;The International Biomass Conference and Expo is the largest gathering of biomass professionals in </font><font size="3">North  America</font><font size="3">. It is a best-in-class professional meeting. Dr. Kukkonen&rsquo;s invited presentation regarding our Giant King Grass fueled, 12 MW renewable, biomass power plant in </font><font size="3">Nicaragua</font><font size="3"> reflects the genuine and growing international interest in this particular project. VIASPACE is keenly focused on making this project scalable and reproducible as we continue with our Nicaraguan partners to make it a reality.&rdquo;</font></font></span></p><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">  </font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.25in; text-align: justify"><span style="color: black"><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">&nbsp;</font></span></p><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">  </font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-align: justify"><span><font face="Times New Roman"><font size="3">The VIASPACE presentation at the International Biomass Conference is available on the VIASPACE website</font><span style="color: #1f497d"><font size="3"> </font><a href="../"><font size="3" color="#0000ff">www.VIASPACE.com</font></a><font size="3">. </font></span></font></span></p><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">  </font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-align: justify"><span style="color: black"><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">&nbsp;</font></span></p><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">  </font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-align: justify"><strong><span style="color: black"><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">About VIASPACE Inc.</font></span></strong></p><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">  </font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-align: justify"><font face="Times New Roman"><span style="color: black"><font size="3">VIASPACE grows renewable Giant King</font><sup><font size="2">&reg;</font></sup><font size="3"> Grass as a low-carbon fuel for clean electricity generation; for environmentally friendly energy pellets; and as a feedstock for bio-methane production and for green cellulosic biofuels, biochemicals and biomaterials. Giant King</font></span><sup><font size="2">&reg;</font></sup><span style="color: black"><font size="3"> Grass is a proprietary, high yield, dedicated biomass energy crop.</font></span><font size="3"> </font><span style="color: black"><font size="3">Giant King</font><sup><font size="2">&reg;</font></sup><font size="3"> Grass when it is cut frequently at 4 to 5 feet tall is also excellent animal feed. The USDA granted approval for planting Giant King</font><sup><font size="2">&reg;</font></sup><font size="3"> Grass throughout the </font><font size="3">US</font><font size="3"> and cooperates in exporting by performing the required inspections and issuing the phytosanitary certificate needed for import into foreign countries. Giant King</font><sup><font size="2">&reg;</font></sup><font size="3"> Grass is being grown in </font><font size="3">California</font><font size="3">, </font><font size="3">Hawaii</font><font size="3">, St. Croix Virgin Islands, </font><font size="3">Nicaragua</font><font size="3">, </font><font size="3">South  Africa</font><font size="3">, </font><font size="3">China</font><font size="3">, </font><font size="3">Myanmar</font><font size="3">, </font><font size="3">Pakistan</font><font size="3">, </font><font size="3">Philippines</font><font size="3"> and </font><font size="3">Guyana</font><font size="3">.</font><span><font size="3">&nbsp; </font></span><font size="3">For more information, please go to </font></span></font><a href="../"><font face="Times New Roman" size="3" color="#0000ff">www.VIASPACE.com</font></a><span style="color: black"><font face="Times New Roman"><font size="3"> or contact Dr. </font><font size="3">Jan Vandersande</font><font size="3">, Director of Communications, at 800-517-8050 or </font></font><a href="mailto:IR@VIASPACE.com."><font face="Times New Roman" size="3" color="#0000ff">IR@VIASPACE.com.</font></a></span></p><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">  </font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-align: justify"><span style="color: black"><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">&nbsp;</font></span></p><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">  </font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"><font face="Times New Roman"><strong><font size="3">Safe</font></strong><strong><font size="3"> </font><font size="3">Harbor</font></strong><strong><font size="3"> Statement</font></strong></font></p><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">  </font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-align: justify"><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">Information in this news release includes forward-looking statements. These forward-looking statements relate to future events or future performance and involve known and unknown risks, uncertainties and other factors that may cause our actual results, levels of activity, performance or achievements to be materially different from those expressed or implied by these forward-looking statements. Such factors include, without limitation, risks outlined in our periodic filings with the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission, including Annual Report on Form 10-K for the year ended December 31, 2014, and other factors over which VIASPACE has little or no control. </font></p><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">  </font>', '2015-05-12 00:00:00', '', '', 1, 1, 1477, 1),
(1478, 'VIASPACE Acquisition of Elite Therapeutics Tabled', '', '<font face="Times New Roman" size="3">  </font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-align: justify"><span style="color: black; font-family: Times"><font size="3">May 26, 2015 - Walnut, </font><font size="3">California</font><font size="3"> - VIASPACE Inc. (OTC: VSPC) Board Chairman, Dr. Kevin Schewe, today provided a brief update regarding the previous announcement of VIASPACE&rsquo;s contemplated acquisition of Elite Therapeutics. </font></span></p><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">  </font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-align: justify"><span style="color: black; font-family: Times"><font size="3">&nbsp;</font></span></p><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">  </font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-align: justify"><span style="color: black; font-family: Times"><font size="3">Dr. Schewe stated, &ldquo;On December 1, 2014, VIASPACE announced that it had signed a nonbinding Letter of Intent (LOI) to acquire luxury cosmetics company, Elite Therapeutics (</font><a href="http://www.elitetherapeutics.com/" target="_blank" title="blocked::http://www.elitetherapeutics.com/"><font size="3" color="#0000ff">www.elitetherapeutics.com</font></a><font size="3">). At that time, VIASPACE and Elite Therapeutics agreed to examine the details and potential benefits of an all-stock acquisition. </font></span></p><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">  </font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-align: justify"><span style="color: black; font-family: Times"><font size="3">&nbsp;</font></span></p><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">  </font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-align: justify"><span style="color: black; font-family: Times"><font size="3">&ldquo;After signing&nbsp;the nonbinding Letter of Intent, Elite Therapeutics, at its own expense, employed a third party valuation firm to assess the value of Elite Therapeutics for a potential acquisition. This valuation was completed late in the first quarter.&rdquo;&nbsp;</font></span></p><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">  </font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-align: justify"><span style="color: black; font-family: Times"><font size="3">&nbsp;</font></span></p><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">  </font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-align: justify"><span style="color: black; font-family: Times"><font size="3">Dr. Schewe continued, &ldquo;While the potential&nbsp;acquisition contemplated increasing VIASPACE&#39;s revenues by succeeding in two, large growth industries, VIASPACE has been steadily moving forward on multiple fronts of its own core business.</font><span><font size="3">&nbsp; </font></span><font size="3">After assessing various pros and cons regarding VIASPACE&rsquo;s diversification into the luxury&nbsp;cosmetics business of Elite Therapeutics, we have decided that the acquisition of Elite Therapeutics should be tabled for now to allow each company to focus on its respective core business&rdquo;. </font></span></p><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">  </font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-align: justify"><span style="color: black"><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">&nbsp;</font></span></p><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">  </font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"><strong><span style="color: black"><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">About VIASPACE Inc.</font></span></strong></p><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">  </font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-align: justify"><font face="Times New Roman"><span style="color: black"><font size="3">VIASPACE grows renewable Giant King</font><sup><font size="2">&reg;</font></sup><font size="3"> Grass as a low-carbon fuel for clean electricity generation; for environmentally friendly energy pellets; and as a feedstock for bio-methane production and for green cellulosic biofuels, biochemicals and biomaterials. Giant King</font></span><sup><font size="2">&reg;</font></sup><span style="color: black"><font size="3"> Grass is a proprietary, high yield, dedicated biomass energy crop.</font></span><font size="3"> </font><span style="color: black"><font size="3">Giant King</font><sup><font size="2">&reg;</font></sup><font size="3"> Grass when it is cut frequently at 4 to 5 feet tall is also excellent animal feed. The USDA granted approval for planting Giant King</font><sup><font size="2">&reg;</font></sup><font size="3"> Grass throughout the </font><font size="3">US</font><font size="3"> and cooperates in exporting by performing the required inspections and issuing the phytosanitary certificate needed for import into foreign countries. Giant King</font><sup><font size="2">&reg;</font></sup><font size="3"> Grass is being grown in </font><font size="3">California</font><font size="3">, </font><font size="3">Hawaii</font><font size="3">, St. Croix Virgin Islands, </font><font size="3">Nicaragua</font><font size="3">, </font><font size="3">South  Africa</font><font size="3">, </font><font size="3">China</font><font size="3">, </font><font size="3">Myanmar</font><font size="3">, </font><font size="3">Pakistan</font><font size="3">, </font><font size="3">Philippines</font><font size="3"> and </font><font size="3">Guyana</font><font size="3">.</font><span><font size="3">&nbsp; </font></span><font size="3">For more information, please go to </font></span></font><a href="../"><font face="Times New Roman" size="3" color="#0000ff">www.VIASPACE.com</font></a><span style="color: black"><font face="Times New Roman" size="3"> or contact Dr. Jan Vandersande, Director of Communications, at 800-517-8050 or </font><a href="mailto:IR@VIASPACE.com."><font face="Times New Roman" size="3" color="#0000ff">IR@VIASPACE.com.</font></a></span></p><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">  </font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="color: black"><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">&nbsp;</font></span></p><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">  </font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"><font face="Times New Roman"><strong><font size="3">Safe</font></strong><strong><font size="3"> </font><font size="3">Harbor</font></strong><strong><font size="3"> Statement</font></strong></font></p><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">  </font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-align: justify"><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">Information in this news release includes forward-looking statements. These forward-looking statements relate to future events or future performance and involve known and unknown risks, uncertainties and other factors that may cause our actual results, levels of activity, performance or achievements to be materially different from those expressed or implied by these forward-looking statements. Such factors include, without limitation, risks outlined in our periodic filings with the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission, including Annual Report on Form 10-K for the year ended December 31, 2014, and other factors over which VIASPACE has little or no control. </font></p><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">  </font>', '2015-05-26 00:00:00', '', '', 1, 1, 1478, 1),
(1479, 'VIASPACE CONDUCTING ENGINEERING PLAN FOR GIANT KING GRASS BIOGAS POWER PLANT IN PAPUA NEW GUINEA', '', '<font face="Times New Roman" size="3">  </font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-align: justify"><font face="Times New Roman"><font size="3">May 27, 2015 - Walnut, California - </font><span style="color: black"><font size="3">VIASPACE Inc. (OTC: VSPC) announced that VIASPACE has been engaged by Clean Energy Solutions Pacific (CES) to provide engineering and design work for a 2 MW biogas power plant fueled by Giant King Grass. CES, based in </font><font size="3">Salt Lake City</font><font size="3">, </font><font size="3">Utah</font><font size="3">, is an independent power producer focused on developing power for frontier and emerging markets. CES has extensive experience in project development and management, engineering and construction of power plants.</font></span></font></p><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">  </font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-align: justify"><span style="color: black"><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">&nbsp;</font></span></p><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">  </font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-align: justify"><span style="color: black"><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">The CES project located in Papua New Guinea (PNG) is to own and operate a biogas power plant and Giant King Grass plantation that delivers reliable, 24/7 electricity to the grid to meet the customer demand profile, under a power purchase agreement from the government electricity company.</font></span></p><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">  </font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-align: justify"><span style="color: black"><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">&nbsp;</font></span></p><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">  </font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-align: justify"><span style="color: black"><font face="Times New Roman"><font size="3">Previously, CES contracted with VIASPACE for an operations plan including the Giant King Grass plantation. VIASPACE&rsquo;s current assignment with CES is to produce a design of the entire biogas power plant including Giant King Grass receiving areas, grass storage, fuel feeding, primary and secondary anaerobic digesters, biogas treatment and storage, engine/generators, control equipment and output transformers to the grid.</font><span><font size="3">&nbsp; </font></span><font size="3">VIASPACE is involved with the selection of equipment suppliers, and providing required specifications and quantities of materials for the project. VIASPACE is also providing operations, maintenance, and staffing requirements.</font></font></span></p><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">  </font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-align: justify"><span style="color: black"><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">&nbsp;</font></span></p><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">  </font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-align: justify"><span style="color: black"><font face="Times New Roman"><font size="3">VIASPACE CEO Dr. Carl Kukkonen stated, &ldquo;VIASPACE can provide complete turnkey solutions to customers including the Giant King Grass plantation and the power plant. Our project in </font><font size="3">Nicaragua</font><font size="3"> is 12 MW and utilizes direct combustion of the Giant King Grass to produce electricity. For smaller applications such as for CES, anaerobic digestion of the Giant King Grass to produce methane rich biogas that fuels an engine that turns a generator to produce electricity is the right solution. We are pleased to be supporting Clean Energy Solutions Pacific. Their project development, construction and operations expertise, and on the ground presence in PNG, combined with our specific technical expertise and Giant King Grass make a complete team.&rdquo;</font></font></span></p><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">  </font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-align: justify"><span style="color: black"><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">&nbsp;</font></span></p><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">  </font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-align: justify"><font face="Times New Roman"><font size="3">CES Chief Operations Officer McCabe Cox reports, &quot;Our biogas power plant will provide badly needed base load power for a remote area in </font><font size="3">Papua   New Guinea</font><font size="3">. It is a clean and renewable alternative to oil-based electricity, and the power plant and Giant King Grass plantation provide needed jobs. We have been working with VIASPACE on the project for more than one year. It makes sense to have our fuel supplier also involved in the design, engineering, and equipment selection for our power plant.&nbsp; Having VIASPACE providing this service for our company has proven to be very efficient, practical, and cost effective.&quot;</font></font></p><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">  </font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-align: justify"><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">&nbsp;</font></p><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">  </font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-align: justify"><font face="Times New Roman"><font size="3">VIASPACE Chairman, Dr. Kevin Schewe, commented, &ldquo;Our project with CES in Papua New </font><font size="3">Guinea</font><font size="3"> has taken more than a year to materialize. We are pleased to announce that we are now moving forward and playing a key supporting role. This project demonstrates how using Giant King Grass for anaerobic digestion can provide clean, renewable electricity for tropical island locations anywhere there is a need for electricity and a desire not to depend on fossil fuels for power production. In addition, the byproduct of the anaerobic digestion process is organic fertilizer to support local agriculture and the Giant King Grass plantation creates local agriculture jobs/employment. We look forward to working with CES to make this project successful.&rdquo;</font></font></p><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">  </font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-align: justify"><span style="color: black"><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">&nbsp;</font></span></p><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">  </font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"><strong><span style="color: black"><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">About VIASPACE Inc.</font></span></strong></p><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">  </font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-align: justify"><font face="Times New Roman"><span style="color: black"><font size="3">VIASPACE grows renewable Giant King</font><sup><font size="2">&reg;</font></sup><font size="3"> Grass as a low-carbon fuel for clean electricity generation; for environmentally friendly energy pellets; and as a feedstock for bio-methane production and for green cellulosic biofuels, biochemicals and biomaterials. Giant King</font></span><sup><font size="2">&reg;</font></sup><span style="color: black"><font size="3"> Grass is a proprietary, high yield, dedicated biomass energy crop.</font></span><font size="3"> </font><span style="color: black"><font size="3">Giant King</font><sup><font size="2">&reg;</font></sup><font size="3"> Grass when it is cut frequently at 4 to 5 feet tall is also excellent animal feed. The USDA granted approval for planting Giant King</font><sup><font size="2">&reg;</font></sup><font size="3"> Grass throughout the </font><font size="3">US</font><font size="3"> and cooperates in exporting by performing the required inspections and issuing the phytosanitary certificate needed for import into foreign countries. Giant King</font><sup><font size="2">&reg;</font></sup><font size="3"> Grass is being grown in </font><font size="3">California</font><font size="3">, </font><font size="3">Hawaii</font><font size="3">, St. Croix Virgin Islands, </font><font size="3">Nicaragua</font><font size="3">, </font><font size="3">South  Africa</font><font size="3">, </font><font size="3">China</font><font size="3">, </font><font size="3">Myanmar</font><font size="3">, </font><font size="3">Pakistan</font><font size="3">, </font><font size="3">Philippines</font><font size="3"> and </font><font size="3">Guyana</font><font size="3">.</font><span><font size="3">&nbsp; </font></span><font size="3">For more information, please go to </font></span></font><a href="../"><font face="Times New Roman" size="3" color="#0000ff">www.VIASPACE.com</font></a><span style="color: black"><font face="Times New Roman"><font size="3"> or contact Dr. </font><font size="3">Jan Vandersande</font><font size="3">, Director of Communications, at 800-517-8050 or </font></font><a href="mailto:IR@VIASPACE.com."><font face="Times New Roman" size="3" color="#0000ff">IR@VIASPACE.com.</font></a></span></p><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">  </font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="color: black"><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">&nbsp;</font></span></p><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">  </font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"><strong><span style="color: black"><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">About Clean Energy Solutions Pacific</font></span></strong></p><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">  </font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-align: justify"><font face="Times New Roman"><span style="color: black"><font size="3">CES is an energy development company which specializes in all aspects of energy<br /></font><font size="3"> development.&nbsp; Members of CES have a combined work experience of over 110 years and&nbsp;have been involved in over $20 billion worth of energy development projects as a combined&nbsp;group.&nbsp; Members of the CES team are known as some of the best experts in their related fields&nbsp;and have impressive track records in developing energy resources.&nbsp; CES development work&nbsp;includes environmental permitting, civil engineering, project management, power purchase agreements and project finance. Further information is available on the CES website at</font></span><font size="3"> </font><span style="color: black"><a href="http://www.cespacific.com/"><font size="3" color="#0000ff">http://www.cespacific.com/</font></a><font size="3">. </font></span></font></p><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">  </font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="color: black"><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">&nbsp;</font></span></p><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">  </font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"><font face="Times New Roman"><strong><font size="3">Safe</font></strong><strong><font size="3"> </font><font size="3">Harbor</font></strong><strong><font size="3"> Statement</font></strong></font></p><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">  </font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-align: justify"><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">Information in this news release includes forward-looking statements. These forward-looking statements relate to future events or future performance and involve known and unknown risks, uncertainties and other factors that may cause our actual results, levels of activity, performance or achievements to be materially different from those expressed or implied by these forward-looking statements. Such factors include, without limitation, risks outlined in our periodic filings with the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission, including Annual Report on Form 10-K for the year ended December 31, 2014, and other factors over which VIASPACE has little or no control. </font></p><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">  </font>', '2015-05-27 00:00:00', '', '', 1, 1, 1479, 1),
(1480, 'VIASPACE ANNOUNCES NEW CEO', '', '<font face="Times New Roman" size="3">  </font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-align: justify"><font face="Times New Roman"><font size="3">July 13, 2015 - Walnut, California - </font><span style="color: black"><font size="3">VIASPACE Inc. (OTC: VSPC) announced today that&nbsp;effective July 10, 2015, Mr. Haris Basit became the new VIASPACE Chief Executive Officer (CEO) and was also appointed to the VIASPACE Board of Directors. Mr. Basit comes to VIASPACE with a proven and successful track record as a senior executive and technology entrepreneur. He&nbsp;has worked as&nbsp;a Staff Engineer at IBM, a Manager at Rockwell International, a Manager at Bell Labs, Vice President of Business Development for OEA International and then&nbsp;Founder/CEO of Multigig, Inc. and Founder of Mobius Power, LLC. More recently, he has worked as&nbsp;a Corporate Strategy Consultant to advise executives of publicly traded companies such as Peregrine Semiconductor and Teledyne to identify new growth&nbsp;opportunities and related partnerships. Most recently, from July 2014 through the present, he&nbsp;became the Founder/CEO of Almaden Energy Group (AEG), LLC. On April 20, 2015, VIASPACE announced that it was partnering with AEG to grow Giant King Grass in the </font><font size="3">USA</font><font size="3"> for animal feed.</font></span></font></p><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">  </font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-align: justify"><span style="color: black"><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">&nbsp;</font></span></p><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">  </font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-align: justify"><span style="color: black"><font face="Times New Roman"><font size="3">VIASPACE Chairman, Dr. Kevin Schewe, commented, &quot;Mr. Basit is the right choice for VIASPACE at the right time. He has a proven capability to innovate, identify key strategic advantages/alliances and&nbsp;raise funds from venture capital firms, private investors, public corporations and government entities.&nbsp;He has built and led world-class technical teams, managed through crises, initiated/negotiated business partnerships/acquisitions and delivered high-margin revenue through diverse business models. He has valuable experience with the licensing of intellectual property. He was a Consultant to Liebman and Associates, the premier clean energy lobbying firm in </font><font size="3">Washington</font><font size="3">, </font><font size="3">DC</font><font size="3">. He is so passionate about being an entrepreneur that he also has been an Entrepreneurship Mentor for </font><font size="3">University</font><font size="3">  of </font><font size="3">California Berkeley MBA</font><font size="3"> students.&quot;</font></font></span></p><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">  </font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-align: justify"><span style="color: black"><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">&nbsp;</font></span></p><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">  </font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-align: justify"><span style="color: black"><font face="Times New Roman"><font size="3">Dr. Schewe continued, &quot;I initially met Haris when he traveled to </font><font size="3">Denver</font><font size="3"> to discuss his proposal to develop a USA-based&nbsp;animal feed business&nbsp;line&nbsp;via a&nbsp;partnership between AEG and VIASPACE. He is focused on the science and mechanics of using Giant King Grass as a highly-productive, water conserving animal feed and understands the business&nbsp;importance of generating high-margin revenue sooner than later. He is already spending significant time at our University of California GKG plot in Holtville, California (Imperial Valley) with plans to rapidly&nbsp;build up the acreage of Giant King Grass and to develop the market and supply chain to customers in the US and internationally. I have been impressed with his background, entrepreneurship and business work ethic and challenged him to join VIASPACE as our CEO with a larger vision to change the world with highly productive biomass both for animal feed and bioenergy. He has accepted this challenge and we will work together to make VIASPACE successful.&quot;</font></font></span></p><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">  </font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-align: justify"><span style="color: black"><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">&nbsp;</font></span></p><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">  </font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-align: justify"><span style="color: black"><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">Mr. Basit stated, &quot;I am extremely pleased to join VIASPACE and work alongside Carl and Kevin to lead VIASPACE. &nbsp;My work at AEG has me particularly excited by the potential Giant King Grass presents as a cost effective animal feed that is less taxing on land, chemical and water resources. I feel challenged and excited to work&nbsp;as CEO of&nbsp;this publicly-traded company and will do my best to help VIASPACE succeed.&quot;</font></span></p><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">  </font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-align: justify"><span style="color: black"><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">&nbsp;</font></span></p><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">  </font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-align: justify"><span style="color: black"><font face="Times New Roman"><font size="3">Dr. Carl Kukkonen, who is transitioning to VIASPACE Chief Technology Officer, commented, &ldquo;I have been working closely with Haris and our animal feed partnership with AEG. In addition, we have also been working together with the </font><font size="3">University</font><font size="3"> of </font><font size="3">California  Giant King Grass</font><font size="3"> project in </font><font size="3">Imperial  Valley</font><font size="3">. Haris is a superb choice to move into the VIASPACE CEO role and I have fully supported and helped facilitate this planned succession of leadership.&rdquo;</font></font></span></p><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">  </font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-align: justify"><span style="color: black"><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">&nbsp;</font></span></p><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">  </font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-align: justify"><span style="color: black"><font face="Times New Roman"><font size="3">Dr. Schewe concluded, &quot;I want to thank Dr.&nbsp;Carl Kukkonen&nbsp;for all his&nbsp;hard work as VIASPACE&nbsp;CEO. He has been a diligent&nbsp;scientist, visionary and pioneer in laying all the groundwork to use Giant King Grass as the world&#39;s&nbsp;most productive biomass/animal feed platform. &nbsp;As Mr. Basit moves into the CEO position, Dr. Kukkonen&nbsp;is transitioning to a position as&nbsp;the VIASPACE Chief Technology Officer (CTO). Dr. Kukkonen will continue to develop our&nbsp;bioenergy business line, especially to insure the continuing development and&nbsp;success of our showcase 12 MW, GKG-fueled, Energia Reino Verde biomass&nbsp;power plant in </font><font size="3">Nicaragua</font><font size="3">. Dr. Kukkonen will also assist Mr. Basit as needed with our active work and expansion&nbsp;in </font><font size="3">Imperial Valley</font><font size="3">, </font><font size="3">California</font><font size="3">. We are enthusiastic and excited to refine and focus our business strategy toward more near-term positive&nbsp;revenue generation with our animal feed business line and getting our </font><font size="3">Nicaragua</font><font size="3"> power plant across the finish line. This new leadership and transition should help us to accomplish these objectives.&quot;</font></font></span></p><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">  </font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"><strong><span style="color: black"><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">&nbsp;</font></span></strong></p><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">  </font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"><strong><span style="color: black"><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">About VIASPACE Inc.</font></span></strong></p><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">  </font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-align: justify"><font face="Times New Roman"><span style="color: black"><font size="3">VIASPACE grows renewable Giant King</font><sup><font size="2">&reg;</font></sup><font size="3"> Grass as a low-carbon fuel for clean electricity generation; for environmentally friendly energy pellets; and as a feedstock for bio-methane production and for green cellulosic biofuels, biochemicals and biomaterials. Giant King</font></span><sup><font size="2">&reg;</font></sup><span style="color: black"><font size="3"> Grass is a proprietary, high yield, dedicated biomass energy crop.</font></span><font size="3"> </font><span style="color: black"><font size="3">Giant King</font><sup><font size="2">&reg;</font></sup><font size="3"> Grass when it is cut frequently at 4 to 5 feet tall is also excellent animal feed. The USDA granted approval for planting Giant King</font><sup><font size="2">&reg;</font></sup><font size="3"> Grass throughout the </font><font size="3">US</font><font size="3"> and cooperates in exporting by performing the required inspections and issuing the phytosanitary certificate needed for import into foreign countries. Giant King</font><sup><font size="2">&reg;</font></sup><font size="3"> Grass is being grown in </font><font size="3">California</font><font size="3">, </font><font size="3">Hawaii</font><font size="3">, St. Croix Virgin Islands, </font><font size="3">Nicaragua</font><font size="3">, </font><font size="3">South  Africa</font><font size="3">, </font><font size="3">China</font><font size="3">, </font><font size="3">Myanmar</font><font size="3">, </font><font size="3">Pakistan</font><font size="3">, </font><font size="3">Philippines</font><font size="3"> and </font><font size="3">Guyana</font><font size="3">.</font><span><font size="3">&nbsp; </font></span><font size="3">For more information, please go to </font></span></font><a href="../"><font face="Times New Roman" size="3" color="#0000ff">www.VIASPACE.com</font></a><span style="color: black"><font face="Times New Roman" size="3"> or contact Dr. Jan Vandersande, Director of Communications, at 800-517-8050 or </font><a href="mailto:IR@VIASPACE.com."><font face="Times New Roman" size="3" color="#0000ff">IR@VIASPACE.com.</font></a></span></p><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">  </font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="color: black"><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">&nbsp;</font></span></p><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">  </font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"><font face="Times New Roman"><strong><font size="3">Safe</font></strong><strong><font size="3"> </font><font size="3">Harbor</font></strong><strong><font size="3"> Statement</font></strong></font></p><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">  </font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-align: justify"><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">Information in this news release includes forward-looking statements. These forward-looking statements relate to future events or future performance and involve known and unknown risks, uncertainties and other factors that may cause our actual results, levels of activity, performance or achievements to be materially different from those expressed or implied by these forward-looking statements. Such factors include, without limitation, risks outlined in our periodic filings with the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission, including Annual Report on Form 10-K for the year ended December 31, 2014, and other factors over which VIASPACE has little or no control. </font></p><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">  </font>', '2015-07-13 00:00:00', '', '', 1, 1, 1480, 1);
