(9, 'Expanding Energy Opportunities', 'VIASPACE is generating positive feedback for its fuel cell power source and humidity sensor technologies from current as well as potential customers in several market sectors including major auto manufacturers, automotive test systems providers, fuel cell developers and suppliers to portable electronics OEMs.', 1, 9),
(11, '', '<p><span>Founded in 1998, VIASPACE Inc. leverages proven space and defense technologies from NASA and the Department of Defense to develop industry leading products and applications that solve complex problems and address critical needs in high-growth industries including clean energy and security. Working through two divisions VIASPACE delivers leading edge technology solutions to the global markets for fuel cell energy supply, fuel cell testing, homeland security, commercial security, national defense, industrial process control, microelectronics, sensor fusion, RFID asset tracking, diagnostics/prognostics and information technology. </span></p><p><span>VIASPACE draws on breakthrough innovation from the U.S. space and defense programs to develop industry leading commercial products and applications. The company has licensed an extensive portfolio of patents and software technology from the California Institute of Technology (Caltech), manager of the Jet Propulsion Laboratory for NASA. <span>Initial investments in these late-stage technologies amount to millions of dollars and many years of top tier R&amp;D, enabling VIASPACE to manage the commercialization process with modest additional investment and greatly reduced technical risk.</span></span></p><p><span>VIASPACE is growing. Business unit VIASPACE Energy offers a line of fuel cell humidity sensor products, operates wholly owned subsidiary Direct Methanol Fuel Cell Corporation&#39;s fuel cell cartridge business, and pursues new opportunities in the alternative energy market. Subsidiary VIASPACE Security, Inc. leverages a NASA-developed inference and sensor data fusion platform to deliver </span><span>new products and applications to improve<span> the accuracy, sensitivity and performance of complex sensor-based systems used in homeland defense, military and security applications including container screening, maritime port security and concealed and improvised explosive device detection. VIASPACE subsidiary </span>IONfinity is developing mass spectrometry technology for industrial process control, homeland security and national defense applications.</span></p>', 1, 11),
(12, 'Welcome to VIASPACE Energy', '<p>VIASPACE Energy has been established to accelerate the growth of its existing direct methanol fuel cell cartridge business, to grow its new instrumentation and advanced battery products business lines (see Products) and to pursue new opportunities identified within the $55.4 billion clean energy sector. The company is identifying and pursuing additional business opportunities in areas including alternative fuels, and new products to conserve energy and reduce emissions.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><a href="../dmfcc.php" title="DMFCC">Direct Methanol Fuel Cell Corporation (DMFCC)</a> is pursuing a significant market opportunity for disposable methanol fuel cartridges and other liquid fuel cell related components and devices. These methanol fuel cartridges provide the energy source for tomorrow&rsquo;s fuel cell-powered portable electronic devices, such as laptop computers and cell phones. DMFCC, through a series of partnerships, is establishing a global network of cartridge manufacturing capabilities, methanol filling and distribution to support the introduction of liquid fuel cell based, portable electronic devices.</p>', 1, 12),
(13, 'VIASENSOR HS-1000 Featured in Fuel Cell Magazine', '<div align="right"><hr /></div><div align="left"><strong><em><a href="../uploaded_files/VIASPACE%20Energy/Viaspace_ViaSensor_FC_Magazine.pdf" target="_blank">Review HS-1000 in-situ real-time gas humidity sensing for Fuel Cells highlighted in December/January issue of Fuel Cell Magazine </a></em></strong></div><p align="right"><strong><em><a href="http://fuelcell-magazine.com/" target="_blank" title="Fuel Cell Magazine">Fuel Cell Magazine</a></em></strong> </p><hr /><h3>Product Focus</h3><p>As advances in measurement technology provide us with greater capabilities, the need for more accurate testing and monitoring of water vapor is increased. VIASPACE is leading the humidity sensing market with the recently introduced, HS-1000 and HS-2000 Humidity Sensor.<span> </span>These devices, provide unequalled testing and measurement accuracy, consistency, and reliability.</p>', 1, 13),
(14, 'Patented Clean Energy Technology', '<p><span style="font-family: Arial">VIASPACE has licensed a broad intellectual property portfolio including 59 issued and 59 pending patents on direct methanol fuel cell technology from Caltech and the University of Southern California. In addition to its fuel cell cartridges, VIASPACE offers patent protection for OEMs and manufacturers of direct methanol and other liquid hydrocarbon fuel cells.</span></p>', 1, 14),
(15, 'Welcome to VIASPACE Security', '<p><span><strong>VIASPACE Security, Inc.,</strong> a wholly owned subsidiary of VIASPACE (VSI), develops high performance real-time inference and sensor data fusion-based solutions for the growing homeland security, commercial security and defense markets worldwide.</span></p><span><p>VIASPACE Security leverages a highly innovative inference engine technology (SHINE) originally pioneered by NASA flight and space applications.&nbsp; VIASPACE has an exclusive worldwide license from Caltech to commercialize SHINE technology for most major applications including diagnostics/prognostics, sensor fusion and homeland defense. Areas of focus include solutions for border, port, maritime, aviation and other security applications.</p><p>VIASPACE Security recently announced the AIMS Perimeter Surveillance Radar solution (by DMT).&nbsp; This small, affordable, easy to install and use system is based on a low power Doppler radar is designed for commercial perimeter security applications. The AIMS security solution is specifically optimized and ideal for monitoring activity surrounding or around critical infrastructure areas such as airports, seaports, military installations, national borders, refineries and other critical industry.</p></span>', 1, 15),
(16, 'Breakthrough Innovation', '<p><span>Sensor fusion combines large volumes of data, observations, and inferences derived from multiple sources and sensors to generate reliable decision-support information in applications where speed, accuracy and ease of deployment are critical. VIASPACE&#39;s SHINE sensor fusion inference engine can process over 1,500 billion rules per second on desktop class computer processors enabling real-time performance unachievable with other comparable commercial products or technology.</span></p><p><span>VIASPACE has added new software capabilities that significantly enhance the functionality, flexibility and ease of use of the SHINE system. The VIASPACE Knowledge Base Editor enables users to accelerate the development of SHINE-based applications and demonstrate capabilities and features for potential new markets and applications.</span></p>', 1, 16),
(17, 'Market-Driven Innovation', '<p>Meeting the challenge for new long range and fully integrated perimeter surveillance solutions, the VIASPACE AIMS radar solution aids and automates the tracking of intruders or security threats.&nbsp; With embedded camera controls in the Radar, automatic slew-to-cue capabilities automatically steer the camera and track intruders.&nbsp;</p><p>The low cost system can be easily mounted on walls, poles or inexpensive cell towers or trailers or vehicles for portability.&nbsp;&nbsp; Web based software client displays radar detections plotted on maps or aerial pictures with color-coded threat levels of warnings and urgent alerts. </p>', 1, 17),
(18, 'Welcome to Ionfinity', 'Ionfinity, a subsidiary in which VIASPACE holds a 46.3% membership interest, is working to develop a &quot;soft-ionization&quot; technology in support of the next-generation mass spectrometers, differential mobility spectrometers and systems dependent on ion level sampling which could not only revolutionize the traditional applications of MS for industrial process control, biomedical, and environmental monitoring, but could also ring in a new era of detection systems for homeland security. The technology combines two inventions made at NASA&#39;s Jet Propulsion Laboratory, which should totally eliminate ion fracturization thus enable the system to provide a 10x increase in sensitivity, a 10x increase in mass range and the ability to miniaturize the product to make it portable and low cost.<p>Ionfinity&#39;s technology could not only enhance and benefit the current mass spectrometer and DMS marketplace, but could also enable the introduction of a new era in monitoring devices and detection systems for homeland security, medical, process control, agriculture, and defense applications.</p>', 1, 18),
(19, 'Product Focus', '<p>&nbsp;The Ionfinity technology is designed to facilitate high sensitivity and specificity in a portable system.  The latest system Ionfinity is working on, a Differential Mobility Spectrometer (DMS) system, will provide ppt to sub ppb level detection within 10 seconds with a system no larger than a shoe box. With its projected ruggedness, low power consumption and cost, the system could be deployed in many applications, where monitoring of air, water or other substances is required. Ionfinity has partnered with Imaginative Technologies, LLC, Sionex Corp., NASA&#39;s Jet Propulsion Laboratory, the California Institute of Technology, and General Dynamics to develop and field demonstrate this capability for the US Army.</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', 1, 19),
(20, 'Next-Generation Chemical Analysis', '<p>Ionfinity is working to develop the next-generation chemical analysis technology, which could<br />not only revolutionize the traditional applications of mass and ion analysis of industrial process<br />control, explosive and toxic gas detection and environmental monitoring, but could also ring in<br />a new era of detection capabilities which far surpass those used today.</p>', 1, 20),
(21, '', 'VIASPACE is dedicated to commercializing proven space and defense technologies from NASA and the Department of Defense into hardware and software products. VIASPACE is developing these technologies into hardware and software products that we believe have the potential to fulfill high-growth market needs and solve today&rsquo;s complex problems. The Company has expertise in energy/fuel cells, microelectronics, sensors and software for defense, homeland security and public safety, information and computational technology. VIASPACE has licensed patents, trade secrets, and software technology from California Institute of Technology (&ldquo;Caltech&rdquo;), which manages the Jet Propulsion Laboratory (&ldquo;JPL&rdquo;) for NASA. This technology was developed by scientists and engineers at JPL over the last decade and was funded by NASA and the Department of Defense. VIASPACE is working to leverage this large government research and development investment &ndash; made originally for space and defense applications &ndash; into commercial products.', 1, 21),
(22, '', '<p>Company: VIASPACE Inc. <table border="2" width="193" align="right" style="width: 193px; height: 51px; border: #060bf8 2px solid"><tbody><tr><td><h6 align="center"><a href="http://www.cohenresearch.com/reports/vspc_09-10-07.pdf" target="_parent" title="Cohen Research Report"><em>Read the Cohen Independent Research Report on VIASPACE by clicking here.</em></a></h6></td></tr></tbody></table><br />Year founded 1998 <br />Ticker Symbol: OTCBB:VSPC <br />Headquarters: <br />171 N. Altadena Dr <br />Pasadena, CA 91107</p><p><a href="uploaded_files/investor%20relations/investor-fact-sheet.pdf" target="_blank" title="Investor Fact Sheet">Click Here</a> for Investor Handout </p>', 1, 22),
(23, '', '<p> <strong><u>Contact Information</u></strong> <br /> Investor Relations Contact <br /> Jan Vandersande <br /> Investor Relations <br /> Phone: (800) 517 8050 <br /> E-mail: <a href="mailto:IR@VIASPACE.com">IR@VIASPACE.com</a>  </p>', 1, 23),
(24, '', '<p> <strong><u>Transfer Agent</u></strong> <br /> The Nevada Agency and Trust Company <br /> 50 West Liberty Street, Suite 880 <br /> Reno, Nevada 89501 <br /> Phone: (775) 322-0626 </p>', 1, 24),
(25, 'VIASPACE PRIVACY POLICY', 'VIASPACE Inc. has created this privacy policy (the &ldquo;Policy&rdquo;) in order to demonstrate our commitment to customer privacy. Privacy on the VIASPACE website (the &ldquo;Site&rdquo;) is of great importance to us. Because we gather important information from our visitors and customers, we have established this Policy as a means to communicate our information gathering and dissemination practices. We reserve the right to change this Policy and will provide notification on the Site of the change at least thirty (30) business days prior to the change taking effect.', 1, 25),
(26, 'COLLECTED INFORMATION ', '<p> We may ask you to register or to provide personal information and preferences when you visit certain areas of VIASPACE.com, request information, or subscribe to email news update system(s). Specifically, VIASPACE may ask you to provide the following information: [Please include all personal information that may be collected at the site] (the foregoing and any additional information requested by VIASPACE, &ldquo;Personal Information&rdquo;).</p> <p> When you provide VIASPACE with your Personal Information, and you do not &lsquo;opt out,&rsquo; VIASPACE and VIASPACE representatives and affiliates may use the provided information to alert you to updated information, new products and services, and other VIASPACE information. Beyond its representatives and affiliates, VIASPACE does not offer or allow the selling of any user-provided information to third parties. VIASPACE complies with the CAN-SPAM Act of 2003 in all email communications. VIASPACE respects the rights users give us when opting to receive e-mail communications and enforces internal policies to preserve those rights. It is our objective to retain the long-term ability to continue to communicate with our users. </p>', 1, 26),
(27, 'RESUME SUBMISSIONS', 'If you send a resume in response to a job opening posted on our Site, we will retain your Personal Information only for the purpose of filling the job opening and will not use it for any other purpose.   Please note that submission of a resume will not be via a secure site and we cannot guarantee that others will not view the data while it is being transmitted.  For that reason, we discourage the use of Social Security Numbers and other sensitive information in online resume transmissions.', 1, 27),
(28, 'COOKIES', 'When you interact with the Site, we strive to make that experience easy and meaningful. When you come to our Site, our web server sends a cookie to your computer. Cookies are files that web browsers place on a computer&rsquo;s hard drive and are used to tell us whether customers and visitors have visited the Site previously. VIASPACE uses the data collected from web server logs and client-side cookies in aggregate form only and does not collect any personally identifiable information. We may use this information to help us better understand what users are seeking and learning at our Site and helps us identify potential navigation issues.  Further, we may utilize the services of partners to help manage and optimize our Site and communications.  Although our partners may log the information coming from the Site on our behalf, we control how that data may and may not be used. Any such partners are not permitted to use this information for any purpose other than to provide this service to us and these third parties are required to keep the information confidential.', 1, 28),
(29, 'PRIVACY', '<p> VIASPACE will always protect the Personal Information that you share with us. VIASPACE stores information internally in a controlled, secure environment. As noted above in connection with the analysis of our Site, we might occasionally hire other companies to provide services on our behalf, including packaging, mailing and delivering, answering customer questions about products or services, sending postal mail and processing event registration. We will only provide those companies the information they need to deliver the service, and they are prohibited from using that information for any other purpose.</p> <p> Phone numbers, e-mail addresses, and postal addresses are never shared with outside entities except as set out in this Policy. Though we make every effort to preserve user privacy, we may need to disclose your Personal Information when required by law wherein we have a good-faith belief that such action is necessary to comply with a current judicial proceeding, a court order or legal process served on our Site. </p>', 1, 29),
(30, 'THIRD PARTY LINKS ', 'As a resource to our visitors, we provide links to other websites.  The policies and procedures we describe here do not apply to those sites.  We suggest checking the privacy policies on each linked site directly for information on their privacy, security, data collection and distribution policies.', 1, 30),
(31, 'CHILDREN', 'You should be aware that this Site is not intended for, or designed to attract, children under the age of 13.  ', 1, 31),
(32, 'OPT-OUT POLICY', 'VIASPACE offers its visitors and customers a means to choose how we may use information provided. If, at any time after providing us with your Personal Information, you change your mind about receiving information from us or about sharing your information with third parties, send us a request specifying your new choice. Simply send your request to [<a href="mailto:info@VIASPACE.com">info@VIASPACE.com</a> ].', 1, 32),
(33, 'FEEDBACK', 'VIASPACE would like to receive your comments and questions about this Privacy Policy. Please address comments or questions regarding the VIASPACE Privacy Policy to info@VIASPACE.com. VIASPACE may occasionally update, amend, or change this Privacy Policy based on user feedback and as needed or appropriate. If we decide to materially change our Privacy Policy, we will post those changes here. We will use information in accordance with the version of our Privacy Policy under which the information was collected. Users will always have a choice as to whether or not we use their information in accordance with, and in respect to, the posted Privacy Policy.', 1, 33),
(34, 'PLEASE REVIEW BEFORE USING THIS SITE', '<p>These terms and conditions apply to your use of the website at www.viaspace.com (the &ldquo;Site&rdquo;), operated by VIASPACE Inc., a Nevada Corporation with its principal place of business at 171 North Altadena Dr., Suite 101, Pasadena, CA 91107, and its subsidiaries (referred to below as &ldquo;VIASPACE&rdquo;,&rdquo; &ldquo;we,&rdquo; &ldquo;our&rdquo; and &ldquo;us&rdquo;).   </p>  <p>YOUR USE OF OUR SITE MEANS THAT YOU ACCEPT AND ARE LEGALLY BOUND BY THE FOLLOWING TERMS AND CONDITIONS (OUR &ldquo;TERMS OF USE&rdquo;) AND OUR PRIVACY POLICY [INSERT LINK].  IF YOU DO NOT WISH TO ACCEPT OUR TERMS OF USE AND/OR OUR PRIVACY POLICY, YOU MUST NOT SUBMIT ANY INFORMATION TO US AND YOU MUST LEAVE THIS SITE IMMEDIATELY.</p>', 1, 34),
