(263, '', 'e-Fuel Cell Technologies is a supply chain manager and distributor of a wide variety of consumer electronic and fuel cell products  for major companies, universities, truck manufacturers and transportation operators in Malaysia. e-Fuel Cell Technologies is marketing software products for VIASPACE Security and distribution of VIASPACE Energy&#39;s line of test equipment and Direct Methanol Fuel Cell Corporation&#39;s line of fuel cell cartridges and other fuel cell products. e-Fuel Cell Technologies has a significant presence in Malaysia and throughout SE Asia. ', 1, 263),
(264, '', ' As a professional energy solution provider, Antig strives to provide cleaner and more efficient energy solutions that power our clients&#39; products, ranging from the application of future energy solutions to the improvement of current energy solutions. Antig&#39;s current focus is on Direct Methanol Fuel Cell (DMFC) technology-a simple, clean, and efficient energy projected to power devices ranging from portable electronics to stationary and residential applications soon. As the professional DMFC solution provider, Antig combines in-depth knowledge on fuel cell material science and reliable manufacturing process to bring about the truly commercialized DMFC Solution', 1, 264),
(265, '', 'INER&#39;s primary R&amp;D objectives are maintaining nuclear safety, innovating environment and energy technology, as well as promoting nuclear technologies in civilian application.INER has three technology centers and one marketing center. The three technology centers are Nuclear Safety, Environment and Energy, and Radiation Application. These three centers along with the existing eleven functional divisions operate in matrices. The marketing center is mainly focusing on technology sales and promotion. ', 1, 265),
(266, '', 'Tokai Bussan, a publicly listed company on the Nagoya Stock exchange, engages in development and sales of computer and microcomputer applied systems, design, development and sales of software systems, and development, sales, import and export of electronic devices and high-performance materials. ', 1, 266),
(267, '', 'Our activities in this field consist mainly of engineering related to development and production equipment for secondary batteries, Ni-Cd batteries, Ni-MH batteries, Li-ion batteries, polymer batteries, double electrolytic condensers, fuel batteries, and solar batteries, etc. and the sale of related materials and parts.Hohsen has also been involved in the development of hybrid vehicles, next-generation low-pollution vehicles, and more practical battery-powered vehicles from an early stage. Gathering information from around the world in the field of energy storage, we offer high-level technological services to clients.', 1, 267),
(268, '', 'Scitech Korea Inc. is a major distributor of fuel cell test stations throughout Asia. ', 1, 268),
(269, '', 'Horizon has built a comprehensive technology and manufacturing platform capable of viably introducing fuel cells into early commercial markets. After providing a first glimpse of its possibilities with the successful worldwide launch of its fuel cell powered tech-toys, the company has now emerged as a world leading producer of PEM fuel cells and electrolyzers. ', 1, 269),
(270, '', '<h1>Distributors</h1>', 1, 270),
(271, 'SHINE Materials', '<ul><li><a href="../uploaded_files/technology/SHINE_Data_Sheet_9_20_07.pdf" target="_blank" title="SHINE Data Sheet">SHINE Data Sheet</a></li></ul>', 1, 271),
(272, 'Field Radar Installation Engineer', '<p>JobID:&nbsp; VSI-040</p><p><strong>Summary: </strong>We are currently looking to build and expand our sensor fusion business around an established perimeter surveillance radar solution.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; We are looking for one or more &quot;A - Team&quot; players who can roll up their sleeves and help us develop and deliver perimeter based Radar and other EO sensor solutions in the field.&nbsp; </p><p>Leading candidates will have the experience, intellect, technical skills necessary, and the passion of &quot;being on site&quot; to step up to the challenge in leveraging your known knowledge and our leading-edge technology to both define the problem, and deliver the solution.&nbsp; </p><p><strong>Job Description:</strong>&nbsp; </p><p>A full time position as a senior member of small group of multi-discipline technologists involved in designing and delivering advanced security applications and tools based on leading edge Doppler perimeter security Radar, Video and IR Camera technology, and other in house developed sensor fusion software technologies.&nbsp;&nbsp; As member of a new field services team, candidate will lead the overall design, installation and systems integration of large scale on-site customer security solution deployments.&nbsp;&nbsp; </p><p><strong>Qualifications and Experience:</strong><br />Candidates should have technical qualifications and experience in the following areas:</p><ul><li>Ground based Radar and Camera surveillance installation and networking </li><li>Radar installation and operation, principles and theory</li><li>Strong background in Networking, Network management and software development,</li><li>BS is Computer Science, EE or equivalent experience</li><li>Other security application qualifications will be considered (Military background, network/physical security, Security Clearance, etc.)</li></ul><p>Candidate must demonstrate strong background or desire in field engineering assignments where travel (Domestic and International), long days, and rolled up sleeves are the norm; and &quot;thinking on your feet&quot; and MacGyver skills often carry the day. </p>', 1, 272),
(273, '', '<p>The VIASPACE Security AIMS perimeter security solution is based on the AIMS Fast-Scan radar.&nbsp; It is a small, low-power, affordable, easy to install and use radar designed from the ground up for commercial perimeter security applications.&nbsp; </p><p>The AIMS perimeter security radar solution is ideal for monitoring activity surrounding or/on critical infrastructure areas such as airports, seaports, military installations, national borders, refineries and other critical industry.&nbsp; The capability to detect movement at ground level of targets such as an individual walking or vehicle or ship moving towards a facility at ranges from 1.5 km -10km or more are becoming an increasing critical component of any physical perimeter security measures. </p>', 1, 273),
(274, 'Key features of the AIMS radar include: ', '<ul><li>The radar autonomously detects movement in a defined area, tracks those targets and raises an alarm if the targets cross into alarm areas.</li><li>Autonomously detects movement in a defined area, tracks those targets and raises an alarm if the targets cross into alarm areas.</li><li>Windows based Client software application </li><li>Fully standard network compliant<br />communication architecture<br />with TCP/IP addressing.</li><li>Built-in camera protocols to automatically point cameras at detected intruders.</li><li>All weather (operates in -40 to +70 deg C temperatures).</li><li>Fully sealed and ruggedized, so neither dust nor weather can enter and damage components.</li><li>Spins 360 degrees in azimuth, and tilts -30 to 110 degrees in elevation for small antennas and +/-15 degrees for larger antennas for complete coverage. </li><li>Designed to operate on land, water, and on beaches, ports, and harbors.</li></ul>', 1, 274),
(275, 'AIMS Perimeter Radar Solution Materials', '<ul><li><a href="../uploaded_files/technology/AIMS_Data_Sheet_12-1-08.pdf" target="_parent" title="AIMS Solution Data Sheet">AIMS Solution Overview Data Sheet</a></li></ul>', 1, 275),
(276, '', '<h4> </h4><h4> </h4><h4> </h4><h4><a href="../page_energy.php?id=60"><u>VIASENSOR BA-1000,   Battery Electrode Health Analyzer</u></a></h4><h5> </h5>', 1, 276),
(277, '', '<p> The VIASENSOR BA-1000 Battery Electrode Health Analyzer is designed to aide the research and development staffs of many companies struggling to get accurate readings on the performance and volatility of batteries of various chemistries. The company believes that there is a strong possibility that the BA-1000 will also serve another purpose as a quality assurance instrument in screening batches of raw materials and finished batteries in the production environment as well.</p>', 1, 277),
(278, '', 'Li-ion battery technology has rapidly become the standard power source in a broad array of markets. While battery performance continues to improve, Li-ion batteries are being applied to an increasingly diverse range of applications, including consumer electronics, military electronics, aircraft, satellites and others. <p>To meet the needs of higher capacity, increased charging rate, lower cost, and improved safety, researchers and manufacturers require a better understanding of Li-ion battery electrochemical and thermodynamic characteristics. </p><p>Until now, little has been known about the thermodynamic behavior of Li-ion intercalation materials during battery cycling. Thermodynamic measurements produce values for entropy and enthalpy. These properties, which are not easily measured by any other means, provide valuable insight to the structural changes related to lithium intercalation.<span>  </span>Furthermore, the total heat of reaction of the battery material can be determined - critical information for battery safety to help prevent (thermal runaway).This information is vital to researchers developing improved electrode materials and by manufacturers requiring accurate, reliable quality control and assurance of batteries.</p><p>The VIASPACE Battery Electrode Health Analyzer (BA-1000) is the first instrument of its kind that can measure entropy and enthalpy in an electrochemical cell. This cost-effective solution provides detailed information that is needed in the battery industry and cannot be obtained by any other known method.</p><p>The initial version of the BA-1000 is designed to study Li-ion and other battery chemistries in small form factors such as coin cells or small laminated sheet type cells. Future models will incorporate other battery form factors and sizes. </p><p>&nbsp;</p>', 1, 278),
(279, 'VIASPACE BA-1000 Battery Analyzer is: ', '<ul><li><span style="color: #221e1f; font-family: ''Times New Roman''">A revolutionary and innovative new technique for measuring entropy and enthalpy of intercalation in batteries and in half cells at any state of charge.</span></li><li><span style="color: #221e1f; font-family: ''Times New Roman''">Based on patent pending technology invented by leading researchers at California Institute of Technology in Pasadena, CA, and CNRS in Grenoble, France, and licensed to VIASPACE</span></li><li><span style="color: #221e1f; font-family: ''Times New Roman''">Powerful, simple and straightforward to use and operate.&nbsp; <br />The BA-1000 is an accurate alternative to other sometimes difficult and expensive techniques such as X-ray diffraction, neutron diffraction and calorimetry.&nbsp; The BA-1000, with its very small footprint will save much needed laboratory space, technique-specific expertise, and money. </span></li><li><span style="color: #221e1f; font-family: ''Times New Roman''">A non-destructive high resolution technique preserving the battery sample and providing precise information. </span></li></ul>', 1, 279),
(280, 'How does the BA-1000 Battery Analyzer work? ', 'The voltage of a half-cell or a battery at rest, known as open circuit voltage (OCV), is measured as a function of temperature. The equilibrium open-circuit voltage is the difference in chemical potential of lithium atoms in the anode and in the cathode. By making measurements at different temperatures, the enthalpy and entropy contributions to the free energy of intercalation can be determined independently as functions of the lithium concentration. <h4>The BA-1000: </h4><ul><li><div style="color: #221e1f; tab-stops: list .5in">Tests up to four cells simultaneously. </div></li><li><div style="color: #221e1f; tab-stops: list .5in">Has up to 1A charge/discharge capability. </div></li><li><div style="color: #221e1f; tab-stops: list .5in">Covers a temperature range from 0C to 40C. </div></li><li><div style="color: #221e1f; tab-stops: list .5in">Is complete with easy to use application software designed to ensure reliable data acquisition and to provide a powerful data analysis tool. </div></li></ul>', 1, 280),
(283, 'Dr. Francis J. Harvey', '<p>Dr. Francis J. Harvey served as the 19th Secretary of the Army from November 2004 to March 2007.&nbsp; As the Secretary, Dr. Harvey was responsible for the Department of the Army&#39;s annual budget, which in Fiscal Year 2007 was over $200 billion.</p><p>He led a work force of over one million active duty, Army National Guard, and Army Reserve Soldiers, 240,000 Department of the Army civilian employees and approximately 200,000 contracted service personnel. He had stewardship of over 15 million acres of land and about one billion square feet of facilities. While at the Army, Dr. Harvey applied his private sector expertise and experience in leading, managing and changing large organizations to transform the business side of the Army as well as to update its leadership development programs.&nbsp; </p><p>The majority of his business career was spent with the Westinghouse Electric Corporation, where he retired in 1997 as the Chief Operating Officer of the Industries and Technology Group.&nbsp; Just prior to becoming the Secretary, Dr. Harvey served on several corporate boards including three portfolio companies of the Carlyle Group.&nbsp; Between 1997 and 2004, he served on total of ten different corporate and non-corporate boards</p><p>Dr. Harvey earned his doctorate from the University of Pennsylvania, and his Bachelor of Science from the University of Notre Dame in Metallurgy, Metallurgical Engineering and Material Sciences. </p>', 1, 283);
